embeds.title: Kalendar Help
embeds.description: For any extra questions, join the Kalendar server: https://discord.gg/7hw7zH4P8w

fields.name: !addSolverChannel
fields.value: Ads the channel the message is in to listen for `kvi`, `ksolve [url]`, and `kfix`.

fields.name: !removeSolverChannel
fields.value: Removes the channel the message is in to **NOT** listen for `kvi`, `ksolve [url]`, and `kfix`.

fields.name: !invite
fields.value: Gives you the link to add Kalendar to your own server~

fields.name: !whitelistFreeTrial [!wlFreeTrial]
fields.value: Gives you 3 days free trial with the bot.

fields.name: !whitelistRemaining [!wlr]
fields.value: Tells you how much remaining time you have for your whitelist subscription.

fields.name: ksolve
fields.value: NOTE NO `!`, for premium users. Include the image url like `ksolve [url]`.

fields.name: kfix
fields.value: NOTE NO `!`, this will look at your latest successful date and use that as a base image. It'll also take in arguments. These can be found in the Kalendar server #how-to-fix channel.

fields.name: !afl
fields.value: If you finish a date in a server that Kalendar can see, this command tells you the remaining time before you can do another date for that character.

fields.name: !set [name] [value]
fields.value: Set Kalendar settings, for more information, do just `!set`

fields.name: !copy
fields.value: If you set `copyType` and `phone`, this is a fast way to get a message you can copy.

fields.name: !frames [list of bits]
fields.value:
1. No bits => all frames
2. 1 bit => all frames that include that bit
3. >= 2 bits => all frames that use some combinations of those bits.

fields.name: !bits
fields.value: Adds up a given list of bits

fields.name: prefix
fields.value:
Tells you the prefix for Kalendar in this server. <@874184247731171348> will always work as a prefix.
Use this with a new prefix to set it. Example:
`!prefix ka-`
will set the prefix to `ka-`
